Subject: LN2 Volunteer Training
Description: Come learn how to make LN2 Ice Cream so you can volunteer to help!  Speakers include:Sarah Elkins, Phil Salkie, Ariel Landau, Jen Hamilton - Track: Food  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: LN2 Fantasy and Science Fiction Ice Cream
Description: Liquid nitrogen 'ice cream' featuring flavors found in your favorite Fantasy and Science Fiction Universes: Butterbeer, Pangalactic Gargleblaster, and Sonic Screwdriver. These flavors all include alcohol - 21+ only.  Speakers include:Sarah Elkins, Phil Salkie, Ariel Landau, Jen Hamilton - Track: Food  - Duration: 1 hour and 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Troubleshooting in Tech, Health, and Beyond
Description: What do medical diagnoses and fixing build breaks have in common? Sarah (configuration management specialist) and Jennifer (medical doctor) will talk about approaches for figuring out whether something's wrong, what is wrong, and possible fixes/treatments. Bonus: how to ask for help (in a way that will help people help you!)  Speakers include:Jen Hamilton, Sarah Elkins - Track: Tech, Life  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: Projector

Subject: LN2 Inclusive Ice Cream
Description: Liquid nitrogen 'ice cream' made with dairy and/or sugar alternatives (soda slushies, soy milk, coconut milk, agave nectar, stevia). Alternative ingredients also available at other LN2 sessions, just ask!  Speakers include:Sarah Elkins, Phil Salkie, Ariel Landau, Jen Hamilton - Track: Food  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: PowerPoint Improv
Description: Volunteer presenters pick a slide deck they've never seen before from a list of titles on a variety of topics, and improv a comedic or serious presentation for up to 5 minutes. They don't have to stick to the slides, as they're just a prop! Audience members then ask questions about each presentation, or about the price of tea in China -- they can improv, too! As improvisations accumulate, we can build off each others' topics and Q&A sessions. Come play with us!  Speakers include:Sarah Elkins, Cylithria Dubois - Track: Gaming  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
